# Uber Go Style

Source: <https://github.com/uber-go/guide/blob/master/style.md>. For full rules with Bad/Good examples, read these topic files at the repo root: [style.md](mdc:style.md) · [guidelines.md](mdc:guidelines.md) · [errors.md](mdc:errors.md) · [concurrency.md](mdc:concurrency.md) · [performance.md](mdc:performance.md) · [testing.md](mdc:testing.md).

## Decision defaults

- Empty slice → return `nil`, not `[]T{}`. Check with `len(s) == 0`.
- Zero-value struct → `var x T`, not `T{}`.
- Pointer struct → `&T{Field: v}`, not `new(T)`.
- Wrap error → `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)`. Never `"failed to"`.
- Goroutine → stop signal + wait mechanism. Always.
- Mutex → non-pointer field, never embedded, named `mu`.
- Channel → size 0 or 1. Larger needs justification.
- Enum → start at `iota + 1` unless 0 is meaningful.
- Exit → only in `main()`, ideally once via `run()` helper.
- Time → `time.Duration` / `time.Time`. If forced to int (JSON), suffix unit: `IntervalMillis`.
- Type assertion → comma-ok always: `t, ok := i.(string)`.
- Marshaled struct field → tag it (`json:"..."`, `yaml:"..."`).

## Style

- Soft 99-char lines.
- 2 import groups: stdlib, then everything else, blank line between.
- Package names: lowercase, singular. Never `util`/`common`/`shared`/`lib`.
- Group similar declarations (`const`, `var`, `type`).
- Reduce nesting via early returns / `continue`.
- No `else` if both branches assign the same variable.
- Prefix unexported globals with `_` (errors are exceptions: `errFoo`).
- Embedded fields at top of struct, blank line before regular fields. Never embed a mutex.
- Always use field names for struct init; omit zero-value fields.
- Raw string literals to avoid escaping.
- Format strings outside `Printf` calls must be `const`.

## Errors

- Return as-is when no context to add.
- Wrap with `%w` when caller may match (default for most wrapping).
- Wrap with `%v` to deliberately obfuscate.
- Drop `"failed to"` from messages — pile up uselessly.
- Naming: exported global → `ErrFoo`. Unexported global → `errFoo` (no underscore). Custom type → `FooError`.
- **Handle once**: never `log + return`. Either degrade gracefully, or wrap and return.

## Concurrency

- `sync.Mutex` zero value is valid — never `new(sync.Mutex)`.
- Prefer `go.uber.org/atomic` (`atomic.Bool` etc.) for type safety.
- No goroutines in `init()`. Expose a type with `Shutdown()` instead.
- Multiple goroutines → `sync.WaitGroup`. One → `chan struct{}` closed on exit.
- Copy slices/maps at boundaries when receiving for storage or returning internal state.

## Performance (hot path only)

- `strconv.Itoa` over `fmt.Sprint`.
- Hoist `[]byte("literal")` constants out of loops.
- Capacity hints: `make([]T, 0, n)`, `make(map[K]V, n)`.

## Testing

- Table-driven with subtests for repeated logic. `tests` / `tt` / `give` / `want`.
- Don't pile branching paths (`shouldCallX`, `setupMocks`) into a table — split.
- `t.Fatal` / `t.FailNow`, never `panic`.
- Functional options for 3+ optional args (`type Option interface { apply(*options) }`).

## Avoid

Mutable globals · embedding in public structs · built-in names · `init()` for I/O · panics in production · fire-and-forget goroutines.

## Lint

Run `./scripts/lint.sh`. Linters: `errcheck`, `goimports`, `revive`, `govet`, `staticcheck`.
